@template-eval text
Use template-eval when the desired output is deterministic, sectioned, and assembled from already-known values.
Prefer it for final response assembly, prompt assembly, and report formatting when the required sections, labels, and order are already known.
Use $family or ${family.path} placeholders to insert values, and keep the template explicit enough that an operator can see how the final answer was assembled.
Avoid it when the step needs open-ended prose invention or non-deterministic reasoning.
